external_knowledge:
- "contenders" refers to the participants in the tournament;
- "standing in the event" indicates the rank of the participant in the tournament;
- "messages they've received" are notifications sent to the participants, including the latest ones;
- "update status of these messages" refers to whether the messages have been read or are still unread.

- Standout competitors: Participants whose performance metrics exceed the general average;
- Tally of matches: Total number of matches played by a participant;
- Performance: Measured by the product of total matches played and average score;
- Collective average: Calculated by averaging the product of matches played and average scores across all participants.

sql:
SELECT name 
FROM participants 
WHERE tournament_id IS NOT NULL;

SELECT MIN(rank) AS lowest_rank
FROM rankings
WHERE participant_id = 1;

SELECT tournaments.name AS arena_name, participants.name AS guest_name
FROM tournaments
INNER JOIN participants ON tournaments.tournament_id = participants.tournament_id;

SELECT tournaments.name, analytics.win_loss_record
FROM tournaments
JOIN analytics ON tournaments.tournament_id = analytics.tournament_id;

SELECT p.participant_id, p.name, COUNT(DISTINCT p.tournament_id) AS total_tournaments
FROM participants p
GROUP BY p.participant_id, p.name;
